# Efficiency Overhaul — [main.py](file:///home/adhiraj-singh/track_project/main.py) Object Tracker

> **Goal:** Maximize FPS on a minimal CPU-only laptop while keeping YOLOv8 + DeepSORT tracking functional.

---

## Current Bottlenecks

| Bottleneck | Impact | Root Cause |
|---|---|---|
| YOLO runs on **every frame** | ~70% of total time | No frame-skip logic |
| Inference on **full resolution** | Wasted cycles on 1080p+ | No downscaling |
| **Synchronous** capture + inference | I/O blocks processing | Single-threaded loop |
| PyTorch [.pt](file:///home/adhiraj-singh/track_project/yolov8n.pt) model overhead | Slow CPU inference | No ONNX/quantization |
| Duplicate logic in [main.py](file:///home/adhiraj-singh/track_project/main.py) + [track.py](file:///home/adhiraj-singh/track_project/track.py) | Maintenance burden | No shared module |
| BGR→RGB conversion on every frame | Minor but avoidable | Always performed |

---

## New Architecture

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph Thread1["📹 Capture Thread"]
        C1["cv2.VideoCapture.read()"] --> C2["Resize to process_width"]
        C2 --> C3["Push to frame_queue"]
    end

    subgraph MainThread["🧠 Main Thread (Qt Event Loop)"]
        Q1["QTimer tick (adaptive)"] --> Q2["Pop from frame_queue"]
        Q2 --> Q3{"tracking_enabled?"}
        Q3 -->|Yes| Q4["Skip frame? (frame_skip counter)"]
        Q4 -->|Process| Q5["ONNX / YOLO Inference"]
        Q4 -->|Skip| Q6["Reuse last annotations"]
        Q5 --> Q7["DeepSORT update_tracks()"]
        Q7 --> Q8["Draw + FPS overlay"]
        Q3 -->|No| Q8
        Q6 --> Q8
        Q8 --> Q9["Display on QLabel"]
    end

    C3 -.->|thread-safe queue| Q2

    style Thread1 fill:#1a1a2e,stroke:#e94560,color:#fff
    style MainThread fill:#16213e,stroke:#0f3460,color:#fff
```

---

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Core Tracking Module (shared logic)

#### [NEW] [core.py](file:///home/adhiraj-singh/track_project/core.py)

Extract all YOLO + DeepSORT logic into a reusable module:

- `TrackerCore` class: loads model, runs inference, updates DeepSORT, draws
- Supports both [.pt](file:///home/adhiraj-singh/track_project/yolov8n.pt) (PyTorch) and `.onnx` (ONNX Runtime) inference
- Single source of truth — both [main.py](file:///home/adhiraj-singh/track_project/main.py) and [track.py](file:///home/adhiraj-singh/track_project/track.py) import from here
- Configurable `process_width` for resolution downscaling (default: 640px)
- Built-in frame-skip counter

---

### 2. ONNX Model Export

#### [NEW] [export_onnx.py](file:///home/adhiraj-singh/track_project/export_onnx.py)

One-time script to convert [yolov8n.pt](file:///home/adhiraj-singh/track_project/yolov8n.pt) → `yolov8n.onnx`:

```python
from ultralytics import YOLO
model = YOLO("yolov8n.pt")
model.export(format="onnx", imgsz=640, simplify=True)
```

> **Expected speedup:** 1.5–3× on CPU vs raw PyTorch. ONNX Runtime uses graph optimizations, operator fusion, and hardware-specific kernels.

---

### 3. GUI Application (efficiency upgrades)

#### [MODIFY] [main.py](file:///home/adhiraj-singh/track_project/main.py)

| Change | Detail |
|---|---|
| **Threaded capture** | `CaptureThread(QThread)` reads frames in background, pushes to `queue.Queue(maxsize=2)` |
| **Import `TrackerCore`** | Replace inline YOLO/DeepSORT logic with `core.TrackerCore` calls |
| **Adaptive timer** | Timer interval matches actual processing speed instead of fixed 30ms |
| **FPS overlay** | Real-time FPS counter drawn on frame via `cv2.putText` |
| **Resolution control** | Slider or config for `process_width` (320 / 480 / 640) |
| **Remove infinite loop** | Video stops at end instead of replaying silently |

---

### 4. CLI Tracker (uses shared core)

#### [MODIFY] [track.py](file:///home/adhiraj-singh/track_project/track.py)

- Import `TrackerCore` from `core.py`
- Remove duplicated detection/tracking code
- Add `--onnx` flag to use ONNX model path
- Add `--process-width` flag for resolution control
- Add `--frame-skip` flag

---

